Priority High:
  * Do not fade in/out if fade length is too short.
  * Use Fragment
  * Show fuda infomation when tapped (kimariji, uta number, creator, key point, how to read kanji)
  * Show yomi info of last fuda

Priority Middle:
  * Show play button on each item of fuda list, and with pressing it, make user be able to play each poem.
  * Add Option: play in arbitrary order
  * In battery mode, the auto play stops when screen is locked
    -> Use val lp=getWindow.getAttributes; lp.screenBrightness = 0.1f; getWindow.setAttributes(l) to turn screen off
       (NOTE: some device locks screen and go to sleep if brightness set to 0.0f)
  * Show same view in any dpi/size display (avoid using px unit), and consider about landscape mode. 
  * Special words such as 'one' 'two' 'red' in fuda sets
  * Split strings.xml since it is too long.
  * Fuda-otoshi mode
  * Yomi-fuda mode
  * Able to customize notify timer (add new, set icons)
  * Pitch and Speed change using picola and FFT (or audio library such as RubberBand or SoundTouch)
  * Use other effects in android.media.audiofx.AudioEffect
  * Create Fuda List from camera photo

Priority Low:
  * Able to change style / theme
  * Show detail of CPU from Android.os.Build when cannot load libvorbis.so
  * Able to read .wav file in case cannot load libvorbis.so
  * Able to record the voice of the player and use it as reader
  * Score the recoded voice (whether it is as good as the official karuta reader). 
  * Able to switch how to play silence (play silence or sleep thread)
  * Fix problem that when "RANDOM" mode, it always does decoding even if unnecessary.
  * Fix problem that when application is in background, the audio skipping occurs. (mabe by changing streamType of AudioTrack, or thread priority of audio_thread ?)
